modules.name: Data.IntMap
modules.comments: An efficient implementation of purely functional maps from integer keys to

declarations.comments: `IntMap a` is the type of finite maps from integers to values at type `a`.
declarations.title: IntMap

declarations.comments: The empty `IntMap`
declarations.title: empty

declarations.comments: An `IntMap` of a single value.
declarations.title: singleton

declarations.comments: Is a given key in the map?
declarations.title: member

declarations.comments:
If a value is available in an `IntMap` at a given tree then `lookup`
will return it. Otherwise, `Nothing`.
declarations.title: lookup

declarations.comments: Like `lookup` but returning a default value if not available in the `IntMap`
declarations.title: lookupDefault

declarations.comments:
Update an `IntMap` by ensuring that a given value exists at a given
key such that for any `IntMap` `m` and integer `k`,

  lookup k (insert k a) = Just a
declarations.title: insert

declarations.comments:
Like `insert` but if the value already exists in the `IntMap` then it is
combined with the new one using a splatting function. The first argument is
the previous value if it exists and the second the new one.

    lookup k (insertWith s k a (insert k b m)) = Just (s b a)
declarations.title: insertWith

declarations.comments:
Like `insertWith` but the splatting function also has access to the
map key where the conflict arose.
declarations.title: insertWithKey

declarations.comments:
/O(min(n,W))/. Delete a key and its value from map. When the key is not
a member of the map, the original map is returned.
declarations.title: delete

declarations.comments:
/O(min(n,W))/. Adjust a value at a specific key. When the key is not
a member of the map, the original map is returned.
declarations.title: adjust

declarations.comments:
/O(min(n,W))/. Adjust a value at a specific key. When the key is not
a member of the map, the original map is returned.
declarations.title: adjustWithKey

declarations.comments:
/O(min(n,W))/. The expression (@'update' f k map@) updates the value @x@
at @k@ (if it is in the map). If (@f x@) is 'Nothing', the element is
deleted. If it is (@'Just' y@), the key @k@ is bound to the new value @y@.
declarations.title: update

declarations.comments:
/O(min(n,W))/. The expression (@'update' f k map@) updates the value @x@
at @k@ (if it is in the map). If (@f k x@) is 'Nothing', the element is
deleted. If it is (@'Just' y@), the key @k@ is bound to the new value @y@.
declarations.title: updateWithKey

declarations.comments:
/O(min(n,W))/. The expresion (@'alter' f k m@) alters the value @x@
at key @k@, or absence thereof.
'alter' can be used to insert, delete, or update the value under given
key in the 'IntMap'.
The following property holds:
@'lookup' k ('alter' f k m) = f ('lookup' k m)@.
declarations.title: alter

declarations.comments: /O(n+m)/. Difference between two maps (based on keys).
declarations.title: difference

declarations.comments: /O(n+m)/. Difference with a combining function.
declarations.title: differenceWith

declarations.comments:
/O(n+m)/. Difference with a combining function. When two equal keys
are encountered, the combining function is applied to the key and
both values. If it returns 'Nothing', the elements is discarded.
If it returns (@'Just' y@), the element is updated with a new value @y@.
declarations.title: differenceWithKey

declarations.comments:
Unions two `IntMap`s together using a splatting function. If
a key is present in both constituent lists then the resulting
list will be the splat of the values from each constituent. If the key
was available in only one constituent then it is available unmodified
in the result.
declarations.title: unionWith

declarations.comments:
Like `unionWith` but where values from the left constituent always override
values from the right.
declarations.title: unionLeft

declarations.comments:
Like `unionWith` but where values from the right constituent always override
values from the left.
declarations.title: unionRight

declarations.comments:
Like `unionWith` but where the splatting function has access to all of the
keys where conflicts arise.
declarations.title: unionWithKey

declarations.comments: Transform all of the values in the map.
declarations.title: mapWithKey

declarations.comments: Construct an `IntMap` from an associative array from integer keys to values
declarations.title: fromAssocArray

declarations.comments: Construct an `IntMap` from an associative array from integer keys to values
declarations.title: fromAssocArrayWith

declarations.comments: Construct an `IntMap` from an associative array from integer keys to values
declarations.title: fromAssocArrayWithKey

declarations.comments: Convert an `IntMap` to an equivalent associative array.
declarations.title: toAssocArray

declarations.comments: Gather all of the indicies stored in an `IntMap`
declarations.title: indices

declarations.comments: Gather all of the values stored in an `IntMap`
declarations.title: values

declarations.comments: A version of `foldMap` which provides key values during the mapping.
declarations.title: foldMapWithKey

declarations.comments: A version of `foldl` which provides key values during the mapping.
declarations.title: foldlWithKey

declarations.comments: A version of `foldr` which provides key values during the mapping.
declarations.title: foldrWithKey

declarations.comments: /O(n)/. Filter all values satisfying the predicate.
declarations.title: filter

declarations.comments: /O(n)/. Filter all keys\/values satysfying the predicate.
declarations.title: filterWithKey

declarations.comments: Checks whether an `IntMap` contains any values at all.
declarations.title: null

declarations.comments: Count the number of values in the `IntMap`
declarations.title: size
